The paper deals with a geometric optimization problem involving points and balls in metric and Euclidean spaces, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. The problem is also a covering problem, which is a classic topic in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper mentions LP relaxation and rounding, which are techniques commonly used in the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-category. The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and hardness of approximation, which are topics in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-categories.
